<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 5:24AM EST  by NWS Burlington</headline>
<description>...Slick Surfaces Expected This Morning...
A sharp cold front moving through will be followed by temperatures
rapidly falling below freezing through the morning. Any standing
water, puddles, or slush will quickly freeze on untreated surfaces.
Untreated surfaces will become extremely slippery and offer
little or no traction. Reduced speeds and greater distance between
vehicles is advised.</description>
